oai_dc:dc.dc:title: FORCES ON A PONTOON IN THREE DIMENSIONAL WAVES
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Eie, J.
Tratterberg, A.
Torum, A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: pontoon
three dimensional waves
pontoon forces
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Wave forces on a long pontoon (floating breakwater, floating bridges etc.) depend to a large extent on the three dimensional wave pattern. There is no deterministic method for calculating wave forces for such structures in a three dimensional sea and laboratory equipment for testing long structures in irregular three dimensional waves does hardly exist.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 12 (1970): Proceedings of 12th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Washington, D.C., 1970.; 101
